For example,
0.9 cannot be represented by a native float, since the binary fraction
for 0.9 is infinite:

scalar  =>  {
                     description => "single item",
                     sigil => '$',
                    },

escalar  =>  {
                     descripcion => "elemento invidivual",
                     sigilo => '$',
                    },

Thus the limits
for Perl numbers stored as native integers would typically be -2**31..2**32-1,
with appropriate modifications in the case of 64-bit integers.

hash    =>  {
                     description => "key/value pairs",
                     sigil => '%',
                    },

hash    =>  {
                     descripcion => "pares clave-valor",
                     sigilo => '%',
                    },
